## 📌 Project Overview

LiveSync Avatar scans the human body in real time using an ordinary RGB camera, extracts a full skeletal structure, and mirrors those movements onto a virtual character inside a simulated 3D environment — entirely through computer vision, with no special hardware.

### Why This Project?

| Problem | Current Solutions | LiveSync Approach |
|---|---|---|
| Motion capture is expensive | $10,000+ suits & sensors | Any webcam is enough |
| Complex setup | Days of calibration | Plug & play, 1 command |
| High latency | 100ms+ with wearables | ≤ 50ms target latency |
| Platform lock-in | Proprietary software stacks | Open source, Python-native |
| Poor scalability | Single-user only | Multi-client via WebSocket |

