## 🏗️ System Architecture

The system is composed of three independent layers. Each layer communicates with the next through well-defined data contracts.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     LiveSync Avatar Pipeline                        │
│                                                                     │
│  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────┐  │
│  │   LAYER 1    │    │   LAYER 2    │    │       LAYER 3        │  │
│  │    INPUT     │───▶│  PROCESSING  │───▶│       OUTPUT         │  │
│  │              │    │              │    │                      │  │
│  │ CameraStream │    │ PoseDetector │    │  AvatarController    │  │
│  │ FrameBuffer  │    │SkeletonBuild │    │  MetaEnvironment     │  │
│  │DepthEstimator│    │MotionSmoother│    │  StreamBroadcaster   │  │
│  │              │    │ BoneMapper   │    │                      │  │
│  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────────────────────┘  │
│                                                                     │
│  ⏱ Target Latency: Camera → Avatar ≤ 16ms  |  Broadcast ≤ 34ms    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Data Flow Map

```
[Camera]
   │
   │  BGR ndarray (1920×1080 @ 60fps)
   ▼
[DepthEstimator]  ◀── MiDaS Model (monocular depth estimation)
   │
   │  RGB + Depth Map (H×W float32)
   ▼
[PoseDetector]  ◀── MediaPipe BlazePose (33 keypoints)
   │
   │  Landmark list [(x, y, z, visibility) × 33]
   ▼
[SkeletonBuilder]
   │
   │  Joint Graph — bone hierarchy (parent → child)
   ▼
[MotionSmoother]  ◀── Kalman Filter (per-joint)
   │
   │  Smoothed joint positions
   ▼
[BoneRotationMapper]
   │
   │  Quaternion rotations per bone
   ▼
[AvatarController]
   │
   │  Applied pose (avatar transform tree)
   ├──▶ [MetaEnvironment]   →  3D scene render
   └──▶ [StreamBroadcaster] →  WebSocket JSON broadcast
```

