**Goal:** Detect all 33 body landmarks in 3D space and construct the bone hierarchy.

- [ ] MediaPipe BlazePose integration and model loading
- [ ] `PoseDetector` class — landmark detection with confidence filtering
- [ ] `SkeletonBuilder` class — 24-bone hierarchy built from 33 landmarks
- [ ] T-pose reference system — design, capture, and storage
- [ ] Debug visualization overlay (`src/utils/visualization.py`)
- [ ] Partial unit tests: `tests/test_processing.py`
- [ ] Pose analysis notebook (`02_pose_analysis.ipynb`)

**Success Criteria:** 33-landmark detection < 8ms per frame, average visibility ≥ 90%

---

### Phase 3 — Motion Mapping (Weeks 6–7)
**Goal:** Convert raw joint coordinates into smooth, anatomically valid bone rotations.

- [ ] `MotionSmoother` class — per-joint Kalman filter implementation
- [ ] `BoneRotationMapper` class — world-to-local Quaternion pipeline
- [ ] Gimbal lock validation tests using synthetic input
- [ ] Anatomical joint constraints (shoulder, knee, elbow angle limits)
- [ ] Motion smoothing notebook (`03_motion_smoothing.ipynb`)
- [ ] Per-step latency profiling — every function timed individually

**Success Criteria:** End-to-end pipeline ≤ 16ms, visually jitter-free avatar motion

